NORTH CAROLINA MUNICIPAL-POWER TRADE GROUP URGES HALT OF DEREGULATION EFFORTS
The controversy this year over electric deregulation in California and other 
parts of the country has led to a major policy reversal for the organization 
representing High Point and the other 50 North Carolina towns and cities in 
the electric distribution business.
